  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I hope the morning walk routine is bringing some calm these days. How was your evening?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Evening was okay. Watched a Bollywood film, \"Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2\". Comedy genre, very light. You know Hindi films?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Light comedies are perfect for winding down. Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2 — was it the same fun as the first one, or a new twist?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The second one is good, but not better than the first. The first was more iconic. The story is similar — a prank and confusion. But some new actors. You should watch it if you like silly fun. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — so the first one was the classic, the second a fun follow-up. Which one do you prefer, and why?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I prefer the first one because it's more iconic and the chemistry between the lead actors was special. The second is okay, but it doesn't have that magic. You know what I mean? For pure laughter, the first is better."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get it — the first one had that special magic. When you think back, which moment from the first film sticks out for you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The scene where the hero pretends to be a ghost and scares everyone — but it's all part of a prank. The confusion and reactions of the other characters are hilarious. Classic *Bhool Bhulaiyaa*. 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — those prank scenes are pure comedy gold. Do you have a favourite prank scene from any other Bollywood film?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, there’s one from *Chennai Express* — the scene where Shah Rukh Khan and Deepika Padukone hide in the washroom and pretend to be ghosts. The way they scare the other passengers is *dubara dubara* (again and again) funny. But honestly, the *Bhool Bhulaiyaa* prank is still the best. I think I’ve watched it 10 times. 😄 Okay, I should get back to work. Talk to you soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — that prank in *Chennai Express* is a classic loop-worthy moment. I get how *Bhool Bhulaiyaa*’s prank feels more magical. What makes it feel like *your* favorite?"
    }
  ],
